The paper deals with power control in small-cell networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The use of a Stackelberg game to model the power control problem suggests a focus on game theory (GT) and control systems (SY). Additionally, the optimization of transmit power and rate may involve multimedia (MM) applications.
